# The Windows field launcher must keep its EXACT bytes: a UTF-8 BOM and pure
# CRLF line endings, with no bare LF. Git's text normalisation (autocrlf /
# eol / working-tree-encoding) would otherwise rewrite the BOM or the line
# endings on checkout, breaking `chcp 65001` code-page handling and the
# double-click experience on a stock Windows box. `-text` marks the file as
# binary for line-ending purposes so Git ships it byte-for-byte.
scripts/OTA检测.bat -text
